<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="94" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="94">
This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Becker, T" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Zoologische Museum Berlin" pageId="14" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 93" title="Neue Dipteren meiner Sammlung." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnz.4830100102" volume="10" year="1921">Becker (1921)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. maculipennis" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" rank="species" species="maculipennis">E. maculipennis</taxonomicName>
from Transcaspia (south part of 
<collectingCountry name="Kazakhstan">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="94">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hervé-Bazin">Herve-Bazin</normalizedToken>
(1923)
</bibRefCitation>
revealed this name as a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Eumerus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eumerus maculipennis" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculipennis">Eumerus maculipennis</taxonomicName>
Bezzi, 1915 from 
<collectingCountry name="Nigeria">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
and named 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Becker’s">Becker's</normalizedToken>
species 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. binominatus" pageId="3" pageNumber="94" rank="species" species="binominatus">E. binominatus</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
is held in ZMHU and has been examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
